## 0.0.141

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.33, xcespcli 0.0.53, xcespproc 0.0.96, xcespwdog 0.0.7 with:
  - xcespserver: license enforcement framework — `LICENSE_ENFORCE` INI flag; router-count gate at commit reads incoming config's license codes; `licenseEnforce` propagated to xcespproc via `SERVER_CAP`; `kFeatureNames[]` extended with mpls/l2tp/vxlan (bits 3–5); `genlic.py` updated to generate licenses for all six features
  - xcespproc: parse `LICENSE_ENFORCE` from `SERVER_CAP`; rebuild against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.111
  - xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.111: license gates in `RtrFrrPObj` (dynamic-routing), `RtrStrongswanPObj` (ipsec), and `RtrRouterPObj` (mpls/l2tp/vxlan) — when enforcement is active and license absent, subsystem reports LLD / skips module load

## 0.0.140

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.32, xcespcli 0.0.53, xcespproc 0.0.95, xcespwdog 0.0.7 with:
  - xcespcli: new `ping` and `dumprt` real-time streaming diagnostic commands; Ctrl+C sends cancel and waits for statistics; `recvStreamingAction()` / `recvFrameOrTimeout()` infrastructure
  - xcespserver: streaming action protocol (`ACTION_STREAM_DATA` / `ACTION_STREAM_END` / `ACTION_CANCEL`) relayed between xcespproc and xcespcli; streaming actions exempt from inactivity timeout
  - xcespproc: fork-based streaming action launcher using PTY; `cancelStreamingAction()` sends SIGTERM to subprocess; rebuild against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.110 (StreamingActionExec, OSPF/RIP objects) and evapplication 0.0.7 (POLLHUP/POLLERR dispatch fix)

## 0.0.139

- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.31, xcespcli 0.0.52, xcespproc 0.0.94,
  xcespwdog 0.0.7 with:
  - xcespserver: server block captured at startup and prepended to PUT hook
    validation payloads so dynamic-routing feature flags are always visible
    to validator scripts (fixes spurious rejections on successive PUTs)
  - xcespcli: navigation TAB/? completion generalised to any depth; candidate
    config included in instance-name completion; improved navigation error
    messages
  - xcespconfig: `validateHooks()` accepts optional `contextPrefix` parameter

## 0.0.138

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.94 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.109: fix charon binding to wrong IKE local address when running in a VRF — `interfaces_use = lo` restricts charon to the loopback interface where the WAN loopback address is placed by `router-id`; prevents TS narrowing to GRE overlay addresses and stops BGP-over-GRE flapping

## 0.0.137

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.94 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.108: downgrade "File exists" on `ip route add local` from WARNING to INFO — when `router-id` matches the WAN loopback, `RtrRouterPObj` already adds the address to `lo`, creating the same local route; the message is now "already present" at INFO level

## 0.0.136

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.94 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.107: fix GRE-over-IPsec — charon now correctly binds to the WAN loopback address (via a leaked local route in the namespace main table), so negotiated traffic selectors match actual GRE outer packets; previously charon used the GRE interface address and strongSwan narrowed TS to 10.102.1.x instead of 10.100.1.x, causing 100% ping loss through GRE tunnels

## 0.0.135

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.93 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.106: fix `show ipsec sa` returning "(no IPsec security associations)" for all routers — the 0.0.134 timeout fix inadvertently added `timeout 8` before swanctl's env-var prefix, breaking the env assignment

## 0.0.134

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.92 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.105: all show queries now have an 8 s timeout via `IpCmd::run(cmd, 8)` — a hung `ip route show` in a bad namespace no longer stalls xcespproc's event loop causing "server disconnected"; also sets `udp_l3mdev_accept=1`/`raw_l3mdev_accept=1` in the router namespace so IKE packets arrive on VRF slave interfaces and IPsec child SAs can establish

## 0.0.133

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.91 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.104: fix `show ipsec sa` always returning empty — env-var prefix ordering bug caused swanctl to never be executed

## 0.0.132

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.90 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.103: `show ipsec sa` no longer breaks the CLI session — `swanctl --list-sas` capped at 5s timeout; packet counter parsing fixed ("packets" not "pkts")

## 0.0.131

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.89 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.102: replace `ip vrf exec` with fwmark-based VRF routing — fixes charon launch failure with "Permission denied" on SELinux-enforcing Fedora when `ipsec { vrf ... }` is configured

## 0.0.130

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.88 / xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.101: defers charon launch until the configured VRF device exists — fixes "Invalid VRF name" timing error when VRF and IPsec objects start in parallel

## 0.0.129

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.87: `ipsec` node supports new `vrf <name>` attribute — charon is launched inside the named VRF so IKE negotiation uses the correct routing table for WAN-addressed DMVPN IPsec

## 0.0.128

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.86: `applyConfig()` guards against duplicate charon launch on xcespproc reconnect — fixes three-charon scenario seen in production

## 0.0.127

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.85: charon now launched with `STRONGSWAN_CONF` pointing to a per-namespace conf (`charon-ns.conf`) — fixes charon restart loop on RHEL where the system-wide strongswan.conf uses a different VICI socket path than Fedora

## 0.0.126

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.84: rebuild against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.97 — `show ipsec sa` now detects `/etc/swanctl` vs `/etc/strongswan/swanctl` at runtime, fixing empty output on RHEL/older Fedora
- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.30, xcespcli 0.0.51, xcespwdog 0.0.7 (unchanged)

## 0.0.125

- Bundles xcespproc 0.0.83: rebuild against xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.96 — `raiseCapsForChild()` raises `CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE` as ambient so charon inherits it and the `socket-default` plugin can bind UDP 500/4500 for IKE
- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.30, xcespcli 0.0.51, xcespwdog 0.0.7 (unchanged)

## 0.0.124

- `install.sh`, `scripts/xcesp-activate`: add `cap_net_bind_service` to xcespproc's capability set — required by charon's `socket-default` plugin to bind UDP ports 500/4500; without it charon logs "no socket implementation registered, receiving failed" and cannot send or receive IKE packets

