## 0.0.109

- xcesp-activate: fix xcespwdog_proc.ini generation — include [process.1]
  (xcespserver) as the first entry; when PROC_CONFIG_FILE is active xcespwdog reads
  ALL process entries from that file only, so xcespserver must be listed there too

## 0.0.108

- xcesp-activate: fix migration patch — after injecting PROC_CONFIG_FILE, also
  remove static [process.2..N] xcespproc entries from xcespwdog.ini; duplicate
  section names across xcespwdog.ini and xcespwdog_proc.ini prevented all processes
  (including xcespserver) from launching

## 0.0.107

- xcesp-activate: auto-generate /run/xcesp/xcespwdog_proc.ini at each start by
  parsing xcespserver.conf (server N / processes routing / count M); xcespwdog reads
  this via PROC_CONFIG_FILE — no more manual [process.N] entries in xcespwdog.ini
- xcespwdog.ini template: add PROC_CONFIG_FILE, remove hardcoded xcespproc entries;
  set WDOG_INTERVAL_TIMER=180000 and add -p 1514 for proper log forwarding
- xcesp-activate: auto-patch existing xcespwdog.ini installations to inject
  PROC_CONFIG_FILE if missing (one-time migration, non-destructive)
- Bundles xcespserver 0.0.29, xcespcli 0.0.48, xcespproc 0.0.79, xcespwdog 0.0.7
  with xcesp-on-rtr 0.0.86 (same binaries as 0.0.104–0.0.106)

